  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed garden building, by reason of its unacceptable size/ width would lead to a 'terracing' effect across the rear of the garden of the listed terrace and an overall scale not sufficiently subordinate to the host building. Given the reduced proportions of the existing garden space, it would adversely affect the setting of the designated  building and would fail to preserve the character and appearance of the Barnsbury Conservation Area. The proposal would be contrary to the NPPF (2021), Policies D4 and HC1 of the London Plan (2021), Policies CS8 and CS9 of Islington's Core Strategy (2011), Policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of Islington's Development Management Policies (2013) and Policies PLAN1, DH1 and DH2 of Islington's Strategic Development Management Policies (SDMP) (2019) as well as the guidance contained within the Islington Urban Design Guide (2017). The less than substantial harm would not be outweighed by any public benefits in accordance with Paragraph 202 of the NPPF (2021)."
  ],
